text.tspan: The CORNETO implementation of CARNIVAL sets the obtention of the solution network as an optimisation problem. On the one hand,
the model tries to get a sign consistent subnetwork as small as possible. In other words, the inclusion of nodes/edges is penalised. On the
other hand, the model tries to minimise the difference between inferred and measured activities in downstream measurements. The
regularization parameter β controls the relationship between these two factors.

g.aria-label: In addition to some other constrains (for example, forcing the inclusion of the upstream nodes), this problem generates a solution space with different solution networks, dependant on the relationship between the two aforementioned factors. This creates a solution space of possible solution networks; the optimal solution is dependant on the regularization parameter.

text.tspan: Given a PKN and a set of measurements, the interplay between size and activity error generates a family of optimal solutions (pink line)
